The Minister of Finance, Budget and National Planning, Zainab Ahmed, has stated that Micro and Small (MSMEs) with a turnover of less than N25 million will be exempted from Compànies Income Tax (CIT) under the New Finance Bill. The Minister of Finance said on a programme of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) on Monday. According to her only companies earning over N25 million per annum would be.subjected to payment of tax.
She said, “Our assessment is that any business that has a turnover of less than N25m needs that break, not being taxed so they can invest in their businesses.” Vanguard  ON September 11 this year, Hajiya Zainab Ahmed, Nigeria’s Finance, Budget and National Planning Minister, briefed State House Correspondents, of government’s plan to raise the Value Added Tax rate from five per cent to 7.5 per cent, i.e. about 50 per cent increase on the existing rate. November 4, 2019 In "News" Mrs Zainab Ahmed, the Minister of Finance, Budget and National Planning, says the nation will not be able to reach 80 per cent revenue performance for 2019. October 14, 2019 In "News" The Federal Government has collected about N12.66 billion  in less than a month after it commenced its substitution of accounts of billionaire tax defaulters in the country. September 24, 2018 In "News"